[node name="ExplanationLabel" type="RichTextLabel" parent="SciCompPopup/Panel" unique_id=1091549926]
layout_mode = 0
offset_left = 11.0
offset_top = -12.0
offset_right = 306.0
offset_bottom = 167.0
theme_override_fonts/normal_font = ExtResource("9_4bm6g")
theme_override_font_sizes/normal_font_size = 15
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "This code uses nested [color=#AAFFC7]for[/color] loops to print a triangle pattern using asterisks ([color=#AAFFC7]*[/color]).

Purpose of the program:
• Print stars in increasing order per line.
Expected output:
*
**
***

[color=#AAFFC7]for[/color] loop

• A loop repeats code multiple times.

Structure:

for(initialization; condition; update)

Meaning:

• initialization → starting value
• condition → checks if loop should continue
• update → changes the value each repetition

Outer loop
for (int i = 1; i <= 3; i++)

Purpose:

• Controls the number of rows.

Flow:
• [color=#AAFFC7]i = 1[/color] → first row
• [color=#AAFFC7]i = 2[/color] → second row
• [color=#AAFFC7]i = 3[/color] → third row

Inner loop
for (int j = 1; j <= i; j++)

Purpose:
• Prints stars for each row.

Important:
• The number of stars depends on [color=#AAFFC7]i[/color].

How it works:
When [color=#AAFFC7]i = 1[/color]
• [color=#AAFFC7]j[/color] runs once
• prints [color=#AAFFC7]*[/color]

When [color=#AAFFC7]i = 2[/color]
• [color=#AAFFC7]j[/color] runs twice
• prints [color=#AAFFC7]**[/color]

When [color=#AAFFC7]i = 3[/color]
• [color=#AAFFC7]j[/color] runs three times
• prints [color=#AAFFC7]***[/color]

[color=#AAFFC7]System.out.print(\"*\");[/color]
• Prints stars on the same line.

[color=#AAFFC7]System.out.println();[/color]
• Moves to the next line after each row is finished.

Main concept:

• The outer loop controls rows.
• The inner loop controls columns or repeated symbols inside each row.
• Nested loops are commonly used for patterns.
"

